---
const qas = [
  {
    q: "Do I even need antivirus on Linux?",
    a: "Desktop Linux malware is rare — but files don't stop at your laptop. If you share documents with Windows or macOS users, run a mail server, use Wine, mount network shares, or pull third-party installers, you're a vector whether or not you're a victim. ClamUI catches infected files before you forward them on.",
  },
  {
    q: "Isn't ClamAV just a server tool?",
    a: "ClamAV is an excellent engine shipped with most distros, but it's historically been CLI-only. ClamUI is a proper desktop interface around it: progress, profiles, quarantine, scheduled scans, file-manager integration — with none of the engine hidden from you.",
  },
  {
    q: "Does this talk to the cloud?",
    a: "No, not unless you explicitly enable the VirusTotal integration. Scanning, quarantine, and audit all run locally. Updates go to the official ClamAV mirrors via freshclam — the same source distro packages use.",
  },
  {
    q: "How does this differ from another GUI I tried?",
    a: "Three things: a system security audit beyond virus scanning, a SHA-256-verified quarantine with a proper restore path, and native Adwaita rendering on both GNOME and Plasma. It's designed as a Linux desktop app first, not a Windows AV port.",
  },
];
---

<section id="why" class="container-tight py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="max-w-2xl">
    <span class="eyebrow">Honest answers</span>
    <h2 class="mt-3 section-title">Why antivirus on Linux?</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 lede">
      The most common comment about desktop AV on Linux is that it's unnecessary. That's half true — and the other half is where ClamUI earns its place.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-10 divide-y hairline border-y hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-white/[0.02]">
    {
      qas.map((qa, i) => (
        <details class="group open:bg-white/[0.015]" open={i === 0}>
          <summary class="flex items-start gap-4 cursor-pointer list-none px-5 py-5 sm:px-7">
            <span class="mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 grid place-items-center rounded-full bg-clam-forest/20 border border-clam-forest/30 text-clam-sage text-[11px] font-mono shrink-0">
              {String(i + 1).padStart(2, "0")}
            </span>
            <h3 class="flex-1 text-base sm:text-lg font-semibold text-white">
              {qa.q}
            </h3>
            <svg
              class="w-4 h-4 mt-1.5 text-white/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180 shrink-0"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"></path>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="pl-[3.15rem] pr-5 pb-5 sm:pr-7 text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
            {qa.a}
          </p>
        </details>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>
